> It also happens with Electron 1.6.7
> It doesnt happen when using 1.6.2

@deepak1556 think it might be related to https://github.com/electron/electron/pull/8724  which shipped in 1.6.3?

It looks like when "hidden" class is removed from webview, it is not become ready immediately on windows.
if i add a small timeout, for the second change click, as in:
```
   $webview.classList.remove("hidden");
     setTimeout(() => {
      $webview.loadURL(LINKS[1]);
    },100);
```

Then, there is no crash.

It happened in 1.7.3, too.

@ferreus 's code worked with mine. (`setTimeout(func, 0)` was also acceptable)
So it seems calling `webview.loadURL()` synchronously occurs the crash.

I tracked down this crash to https://chromium.googlesource.com/experimental/chromium/src/+/58.0.3029.110/content/browser/browser_plugin/browser_plugin_guest.h#153
```
WebContentsImpl* embedder_web_contents() const {
    return attached_ ? owner_web_contents_ : nullptr;
}
```
Which results in null pointer access on LoadURL when the view is hidden (Because it's detached).
This is actually not a matter of race condition. As it's simply enough to hide the webview, then issue LoadURL to crash it.

This will avoid the crash by simply refusing to navigate when the view is not attached.
